cs.LG, cs.GT, cs.NI, cs.AI, cs.DC

This paper proposes an auction-based market model for incentivizing data owners to participate in federated learning. The paper focuses on designing auction mechanisms to maximize the social welfare of the federated learning services market. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.GT (Game Theory), as the paper proposes auction mechanisms. The paper also considers communication traffic congestion, which suggests the category cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper uses deep reinforcement learning and graph neural networks, indicating the category cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper proposes a market model, which could fall under the category cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing).
